88 template<typename S>
89 Trajectory<S>::Trajectory(const std::vector<S> states,
90  const std::vector<double> times)
91  : states_(states),
92  times_(times) {
93  // Warn if state/time lists are not the same length and truncate
94  // the longer one to match the smaller.
95  if (states_.size() != times_.size()) {
96  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: states/times are not the same length.");
97 
98  // Resize the shorter one.
99  if (states_.size() > times_.size())
100  states_.resize(times_.size());
101  else
102  times_.resize(states_.size());
103  }
104 
105  // Make sure times are sorted. Overwrite any inversions with the larger
106  // time as we move left to right in the list.
107  for (size_t ii = 1; ii < times_.size(); ii++) {
108  if (times_[ii - 1] > times_[ii]) {
109  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: fixing an inversion in the list of times.");
110  times_[ii] = times_[ii + 1];
111  }
112  }
113 }
114 
115 // Construct from a ROS message.
116 template<typename S>
117 Trajectory<S>::Trajectory(const fastrack_msgs::Trajectory::ConstPtr& msg) {
118  size_t num_elements = msg->states.size();
119 
120  // Get size carefully.
121  if (msg->states.size() != msg->times.size()) {
122  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: states/times are not the same length.");
123  num_elements = std::min(msg->states.size(), msg->times.size());
124  }
125 
126  // Unpack message.
127  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < num_elements; ii++) {
128  states_.push_back(S(msg->states[ii]));
129  times_.push_back(S(msg->times[ii]));
130  }
131 }

133 // Interpolate at a particular time.
134 template<typename S>
135 S Trajectory<S>::Interpolate(double t) const {
136  // Get an iterator pointing to the first element in times_ that does
137  // not compare less than t.
138  const std::vector<S>::const_iterator iter =
139  std::lower_bound(times_.begin(), times_.end(), t);
140 
141  // Catch case where iter points to the beginning of the list.
142  // This will happen if t occurs before the first time in the list.
143  if (iter == times_.begin()) {
144  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "Trajectory: interpolating before first time.");
145  return states_.front();
146  }
147 
148  // Catch case where iter points to the end of the list.
149  // This will happen if t occurs after the last time in the list.
150  if (iter == times_.end()) {
151  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "Trajectory: interpolating after the last time.");
152  return states_.back();
153  }
154 
155  // Iterator definitely points to somewhere in the middle of the list.
156  // Get indices sandwiching t.
157  const size_t hi = (iter - times_.begin());
158  const size_t lo = hi - 1;
159 
160  // Linearly interpolate states.
161  const double frac = (t - times_[lo]) / (times_[hi] - times_[lo]);
162  return (1.0 - frac) * states_[lo] + frac * states_[hi];
163 }

165 // Convert to a ROS message.
166 template <typename S>
167 fastrack_msgs::Trajectory Trajectory<S>::ToRos() const {
168  fastrack_msgs::Trajectory msg;
169 
170  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < states_.size(); ii++) {
171  msg.states.push_back(states_[ii].ToRos());
172  msg.times.push_back(times_[ii]);
173  }
174 
175  return msg;
176 }

179 // Visualize this trajectory.
180 template<typename S>
181 void Trajectory<S>::Visualize(const ros::Publisher& pub,
182  const std::string& frame) const {
183  if (pub.getNumSubscribers() == 0)
184  return;
185 
186  // Set up spheres marker.
187  visualization_msgs::Marker spheres;
188  spheres.ns = "spheres";
189  spheres.header.frame_id = frame;
190  spheres.header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
191  spheres.id = 0;
192  spheres.type = visualization_msgs::Marker::SPHERE_LIST;
193  spheres.action = visualization_msgs::Marker::ADD;
194  spheres.scale.x = 0.1;
195  spheres.scale.y = 0.1;
196  spheres.scale.z = 0.1;
197 
198  // Set up line strip marker.
199  visualization_msgs::Marker lines;
200  lines.ns = "lines";
201  lines.header.frame_id = frame_id;
202  lines.header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
203  lines.id = 0;
204  lines.type = visualization_msgs::Marker::LINE_STRIP;
205  lines.action = visualization_msgs::Marker::ADD;
206  lines.scale.x = 0.05;
207 
208  // Populate markers.
209  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < states_.size(); ii++) {
210  geometry_msgs::Point p;
211  p.x = states_[ii].X();
212  p.y = states_[ii].Y();
213  p.z = states_[ii].Z();
214 
215  const std_msgs::ColorRGBA c = Colormap(times_[ii]);
216 
217  spheres.points.push_back(p);
218  spheres.colors.push_back(c);
219  lines.points.push_back(p);
220  lines.colors.push_back(c);
221  }
222 
223  // Publish.
224  pub.publish(spheres);
225  if (states_.size() > 1)
226  pub.publish(lines);
227 }

229 // Custom colormap for the given time.
230 template<typename S>
231 std_msgs::ColorRGBA Trajectory<S>::Colormap(double t) const {
232  std_msgs::ColorRGBA c;
233  c.r = std::clamp((t - times_.front()) /
234  (times_.back() - times_.front()), 0.0, 1.0);
235  c.g = 0.0;
236  c.b = 1.0 - c.r;
237  c.a = 0.9;
238 }
